Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.46,0:00:08.23,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Access granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.69,0:00:10.55,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Access granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.81,0:00:12.65,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.50,0:00:21.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Please give us your signatures to \Nkeep Sakura Hall from closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.78,0:00:25.04,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,If two-thirds of all students \Nshow their support,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:28.25,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,we can protest the school's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.86,0:00:29.84,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.63,0:00:32.25,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Please show your support!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.48,0:00:36.07,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,This is harder than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.68,0:00:39.26,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It has nothing to do with \Nthe other students.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.53,0:00:42.21,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I heard Sakura Hall's in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:43.10,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Miyahara-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.80,0:00:45.96,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll support you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.60,0:00:48.11,Sign,BOOK,0000,0000,0000,,We oppose the closing of Sakura Hall!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.38,0:00:49.49,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.51,0:00:52.28,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Miyahara-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.06,0:00:55.05,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.29,0:00:59.06,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.30,0:01:02.95,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell my friends about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.26,0:01:04.55,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.03,0:01:05.76,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.43,0:01:08.48,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Miyahara!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.53,0:01:17.23,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Please give us your signatures to \Nkeep Sakura Hall from closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.08,0:02:51.81,Sign,BOOK,0000,0000,0000,,We oppose the closing of Sakura Hall!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.40,0:02:53.31,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We spent all morning gathering \Nsignatures and only managed three.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.83,0:03:02.65,Eptitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}#20 In Order To Keep Saying We're Home
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:55.88,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiigusa-senpai and \NMitaka-senpai should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.88,0:02:58.55,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,going around the third year \Nclassrooms right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.05,0:03:02.66,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.20,0:03:06.96,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka, what happened \Nto you this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.38,0:03:09.93,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We agreed to gather signatures together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:12.42,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.31,0:03:15.12,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Suimei University of the Arts High School{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.31,0:03:15.12,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,Board Meeting Minutes (2012)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.84,0:03:15.13,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously, the minutes of the board meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:16.24,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.24,0:03:18.04,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Mitaka-senpai was curious about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.53,0:03:21.03,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Reading them should make it clear \Nwhat the board was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.03,0:03:22.75,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You got this from hacking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.75,0:03:24.82,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all right for us to \Ndo something like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:27.18,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think I'd do \Nanything that'd get me caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.76,0:03:29.43,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.43,0:03:30.79,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at the first page.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.61,0:03:35.36,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the specialist's report on \Nthe condition of Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.54,0:03:39.94,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"In the name of safety, \Nresidents should be moved out...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.94,0:03:42.45,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and the building torn \Ndown within five years."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:45.66,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Five years is a long way off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.66,0:03:49.15,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there's no reason \Nfor us to leave in such a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.15,0:03:50.48,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Keep reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.73,0:03:53.69,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Vice Principal{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.73,0:03:53.69,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,I agree. Shiina Mashiro should be moved into the regular \Ndorms immediately and made to focus on studying art.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:03:53.52,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:57.67,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Vice Principal{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:57.67,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,Sengoku-sensei is Shiina Mashiro's cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:57.67,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,Because of this, we have respected Sengoku-sensei's opinions and tried to settle this as amicably as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.16,0:03:56.20,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.25,0:04:00.30,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina's name keeps coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.93,0:04:03.57,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,They're skirting the issue,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.57,0:04:07.43,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but simply put, it seems that keeping \NShiina Mashiro in Sakura Hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.43,0:04:08.75,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,is inconvenient for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.75,0:04:09.47,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.21,0:04:14.77,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The board feels that Shiina using \Nher artistic talents for manga...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.77,0:04:16.98,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,is a threat to the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.57,0:04:21.50,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,They must do something before \Nthe school is accused...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.50,0:04:23.21,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,of squandering Shiina's talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:26.48,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Having determined it to be a \Nnegative influence on Shiina,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:28.73,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,they decided to tear down Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.73,0:04:30.00,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.00,0:04:31.77,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina's decision to \Nbecome a manga artist...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:33.58,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,has nothing to do with Sakura Hall!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.58,0:04:36.95,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The board doesn't seem to think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.95,0:04:38.74,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to explain the \Nsituation to the principal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.74,0:04:39.94,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Kanda-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:46.00,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda-kun, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:50.34,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If I were the principal, \NI would ask you the following:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:53.84,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find out about the \Ncontents of the meeting minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.32,0:04:58.28,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't intend to blurt out \Nthat we hacked into...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.28,0:05:00.22,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the school's servers, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.19,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be even worse off if \Nyou say something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.62,0:05:07.36,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Sengoku-sensei explains \NShiina's manga and Sakura Hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:09.18,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,have nothing to do with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:15.41,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Sengoku{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:15.41,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,As I have stated repeatedly, Shiina Mashiro did not\N begin drawing manga because of Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:15.41,Sign,TABLET,0000,0000,0000,,She began drawing manga before coming to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.54,0:05:10.59,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:15.41,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Chihiro-sensei's persistence \Nhas kept Sakura Hall from closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.68,0:05:17.52,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,So what are we supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:19.38,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just do nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:20.60,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:22.63,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The answer seems pretty obvious to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.94,0:05:27.98,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina's presence in Sakura Hall \Nis their reason for tearing it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.49,0:05:32.64,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The solution's there for \Nall to see, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.64,0:05:33.60,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:37.91,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda, your time is more valuable \Nthan anyone's right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.22,0:05:41.07,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What about your preparations \Nfor the game title screening?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:05:44.34,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It would be smarter to\N settle this quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.34,0:05:47.42,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and focus all your attention on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.24,0:05:49.92,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I said shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:52.80,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.47,0:05:56.50,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Were you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.00,0:06:00.74,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.07,0:06:02.34,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:04.59,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I got Shiho to write her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:04.59,Sign,BOOK,0000,0000,0000,,We oppose the closing of Sakura Hall!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:06.26,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:09.34,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,There are people in your \Nclass who'll support us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:11.79,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,How many more do we need?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.25,0:06:14.81,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,A lot. Enough to fill this notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.73,0:06:17.29,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go ask more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:24.36,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the third years aren't \Non campus at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.92,0:06:28.38,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, getting signatures \Nfrom two-thirds of all the students...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.38,0:06:33.12,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,would mean we need nearly all of the \Nfirst and second years to sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:35.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:38.01,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you do get enough signatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.01,0:06:39.97,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,as long as Shiina stays in Sakura Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.97,0:06:42.38,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no guarantee the board \Nwill reverse its decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.12,0:06:45.81,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.17,0:06:48.34,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The solution's staring you in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.34,0:06:49.83,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you casting it aside?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.41,0:06:54.78,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you care if Shiina \Nleaves Sakura Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.78,0:06:56.82,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.82,0:06:59.14,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.28,0:07:00.03,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's not—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.03,0:07:02.15,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,How can Sakura Hall be Sakura Hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.15,0:07:04.38,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,if someone who belongs there is missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:07.23,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want anyone to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:10.74,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Year 2012{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:10.74,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall Resident List
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.86,0:07:09.43,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I want Shiina and Aoyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.43,0:07:11.93,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki-senpai, Jin-san, \Nand Chihiro-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:15.24,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,and you to stay in Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.65,0:07:17.18,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,All of you are my precious friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.67,0:07:18.69,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you this, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.95,0:07:22.30,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Are your precious friendships so fragile that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.30,0:07:27.05,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you would lose them just \Nbecause a building is torn down?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.05,0:07:27.59,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:32.28,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Such weak bonds would\N soon dissolve anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.98,0:07:34.97,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, they're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.97,0:07:37.72,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you're able to \Nprotect Sakura Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.72,0:07:40.27,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,half of the residents \Nwill have left by next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.78,0:07:43.28,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You should think about that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.86,0:07:47.32,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,They're graduating, so it \Ncan't be helped, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.70,0:07:48.78,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:51.76,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who's leaving, Ponytail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.76,0:07:52.40,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.85,0:07:55.78,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The results of your audition \Nshould be out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.58,0:07:59.57,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If you pass, you'll start working \Nfor a voice acting agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:02.87,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Your financial burdens will decrease,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:05.25,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and you won't need to live \Nin Sakura Hall anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.78,0:08:10.19,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall isn't a place \None chooses to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:12.38,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Once your issues resolve \Nthemselves, you can't stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:16.59,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't much time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.18,0:08:20.39,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It may be better to spend \Nyour time with the other residents...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.39,0:08:24.06,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,instead of wasting time\N trying to collect signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.56,0:08:34.63,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,If I pass my audition, I'll have \Nto move back to the regular dorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.26,0:08:36.39,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'd forgotten all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:39.92,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You should be getting \Nyour results back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.92,0:08:44.75,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Every day when I go back \Nto Sakura Hall, I get nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.75,0:08:47.35,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.35,0:08:51.67,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I promised my dad I'd go \Nback home if I don't pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.80,0:08:56.30,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Whether I pass or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.96,0:08:59.76,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll only be able to stay in \NSakura Hall until spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:01.58,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Aoyama...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.76,0:09:05.06,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll still work hard \Nto get those signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:07.90,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want Sakura Hall to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.90,0:09:10.76,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Can you only stay at your \Ntraining school for two years?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.76,0:09:11.32,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.41,0:09:15.98,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Pass or fail, you graduate after two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:17.03,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.90,0:09:19.65,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's kinda definite, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.06,0:09:23.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,If only they'd let you \Nstay as long as you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.39,0:09:27.79,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I think the deadline forces \Nsome people to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.82,0:09:30.84,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Telling someone to stop when...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.84,0:09:32.55,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,they can't do something is \Na form of kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:39.80,Sign,PC,0000,0000,0000,,Subject: My beloved Ryunosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:39.80,Sign,PC,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro told me about Sakura Hall being torn down.\NIs there anything I can do? \NRita
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.69,0:09:45.63,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke-sama is currently at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:50.48,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,He does not have any time \Nfor a former freeloader.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.48,0:09:51.77,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.77,0:09:55.56,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro told me Ryunosuke isn't \Nhelping them get signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:57.00,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.40,0:10:00.42,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,It has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:03.70,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,If there's some reason\N for it, please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.56,0:10:06.00,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.84,0:10:08.96,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,If Sakura Hall disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:13.12,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke may become even \Nmore alone than he is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:22.01,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you concerned for him, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.91,0:10:30.45,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,A bug has been encountered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.45,0:10:32.52,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Beware of electrical currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.11,0:10:37.90,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,It happened in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.79,0:10:43.62,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke-sama decided to make \Na game with his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:47.53,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,At first, things went smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.17,0:10:52.81,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,However, Ryunosuke-sama's \Nskills were already very advanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.81,0:10:58.55,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and the others were unable \Nto meet his requests.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.37,0:11:06.00,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke-sama was frustrated and \Noccasionally criticized them very harshly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.30,0:11:11.72,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke-sama became isolated \Nand was removed from the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:17.21,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,They never invited him \Nto join them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.81,0:11:23.71,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,I have recovered from my system failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.71,0:11:25.91,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Please do not contact me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:26.58,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:34.08,Saku-main,SHIHO,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.91,0:11:36.50,Saku-main,SHIHO,0000,0000,0000,,You're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.90,0:11:39.33,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Shiho, thanks for signing my notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.73,0:11:43.73,Saku-main,SHIHO,0000,0000,0000,,That's a big canvas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.82,0:11:47.02,Saku-main,SHIHO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to paint?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.14,0:11:52.85,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The screening meeting will \Ntake place on March 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.56,0:11:55.66,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You won't need to make a \Npresentation this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:58.17,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The meeting begins at 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.17,0:12:00.42,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and the results should be posted\N roughly 30 minutes after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:02.30,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let you know as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.74,0:12:06.87,Saku-thought,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina's presence in Sakura Hall is \Ntheir reason for tearing it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.57,0:12:09.37,Saku-thought,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,How many more do we need?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.81,0:12:13.17,Saku-thought,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll only be able to stay in \NSakura Hall until spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.39,0:12:15.96,Saku-thought,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What about your preparations \Nfor the game title screening?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.19,0:12:16.83,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:21.66,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You seem out of it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.66,0:12:23.10,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.45,0:12:27.96,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something bothering you \Nbesides the title screening?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.96,0:12:29.56,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.62,0:12:33.27,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we take a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:34.97,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What? We don't need to...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.56,0:12:37.63,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Two coffees.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.66,0:12:39.91,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.13,0:12:43.24,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.84,0:12:46.47,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I had a similar experience once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.77,0:12:49.62,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Just before graduating from college,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:52.81,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was busy preparing to start this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.35,0:12:55.83,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.40,0:12:58.26,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,a girl I was interested in was having trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.26,0:13:00.50,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,deciding what she wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.58,0:13:05.91,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Should she become an artist or an art teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.54,0:13:11.27,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't have time \Nto worry about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:16.71,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't give up one,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.71,0:13:20.07,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,there must be a way to manage \Nboth without choosing one or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:23.36,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter which...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.38,0:13:27.37,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you choose as long as...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.37,0:13:29.74,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you consider what you want \Nto do and what you should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.28,0:13:33.42,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What I want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.82,0:13:34.47,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:40.13,Saku-main,KAZUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like to do? \NShould we continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.62,0:13:44.91,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:49.55,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Title Screening Meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.78,0:13:49.55,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,March 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.13,0:13:52.10,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's the day before the \Ngraduation ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.21,0:14:01.38,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Today was your last day?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.38,0:14:01.90,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.49,0:14:04.51,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Today was my last day after taking lessons...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.51,0:14:05.71,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:07.02,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.02,0:14:07.74,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:09.24,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Two years, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:12.11,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you say it twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.11,0:14:14.50,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking... that's a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.81,0:14:16.75,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:19.23,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.23,0:14:19.93,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:23.25,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want to \Nbecome a voice actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.90,0:14:25.68,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,In elementary school,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.68,0:14:28.45,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,my teacher complimented me \Nwhen I was reading aloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.01,0:14:30.60,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when it all started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.96,0:14:33.65,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I became more interested \Nin voice-over work...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.65,0:14:36.82,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and eventually decided to give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.24,0:14:40.30,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,When I talked to my father about \Nit, he was extremely opposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:42.49,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,But that just made me more determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.49,0:14:43.62,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Simple, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.60,0:14:46.30,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That momentum might be necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.30,0:14:49.19,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,when you're setting out to achieve something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.19,0:14:50.28,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:52.58,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The same goes for collecting signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.58,0:14:54.49,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take that momentum \Nand give it our best shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.05,0:15:00.21,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be great if we both passed and \NSakura Hall didn't get torn down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.61,0:15:01.29,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.34,0:15:08.32,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:09.59,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.59,0:15:10.71,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:12.72,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking at Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:16.89,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,This arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.24,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.52,0:15:56.35,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.12,0:16:00.02,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.79,0:16:06.70,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.21,0:16:09.43,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I did all I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.43,0:16:10.19,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.16,0:16:13.15,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.75,0:16:17.57,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Aoyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.57,0:16:18.41,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.92,0:16:19.91,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.15,0:16:22.43,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push yourself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:26.39,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,If I cry now, I'll end up\N being good for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:29.92,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to stop \Ngathering signatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:32.24,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,when Sakura Hall might be torn down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.20,0:16:35.39,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to end up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:41.03,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiigusa-senpai and Mitaka-senpai \Nare about to graduate, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.83,0:16:43.45,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to make them worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.87,0:16:46.59,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I want to send them off with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:50.23,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine until graduation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.89,0:16:53.20,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll cry a river after the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.70,0:16:55.41,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, kouhai-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.13,0:16:57.58,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you wearing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.58,0:17:01.83,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I came up with a great idea \Nto get lots more signatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:04.23,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I call it my costume plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:05.98,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,The critters of the forest are watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.98,0:17:08.63,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to gather \Nsignatures wearing that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.84,0:17:09.76,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.76,0:17:11.67,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm not wearing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:13.59,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you definitely will!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.09,0:17:20.20,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us gather signatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.20,0:17:22.56,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us gather signatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.20,0:17:22.56,Saku-overlap,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interrupt their practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.37,0:17:25.06,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,What a situation this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:28.37,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Nanami has so much energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.37,0:17:29.32,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.65,0:17:41.08,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,This is some turn of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:46.35,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Did Misaki tell her, "I'll stop chasing \Nthem if you wear a costume, too"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.89,0:17:49.34,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,"That's not what you \Npromised," she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.33,0:17:53.82,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry so much, Sorata.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.18,0:17:57.02,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,But when I think of how Aoyama must feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:18:00.76,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Aoyama-san's probably trying \Nway too hard to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:06.27,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, she wants to act \Ncheerful for the sake of Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.60,0:18:10.42,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,We should do everything we can, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.34,0:18:15.85,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,If Sakura Hall disappears now, \NAoyama-san will be beyond saving.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:38.25,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Incoming Call
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:38.25,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,International Call
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:38.25,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Former Freeloader
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:33.02,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke-sama, you have an incoming...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.02,0:18:34.89,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,international call from \NRita Ainsworth-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.89,0:18:37.12,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy. Ignore her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:43.14,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.77,0:18:46.43,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,I believe her reason for \Ncalling may be important.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:49.11,Saku-main,MAID,0000,0000,0000,,I recommend you answer her call.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.68,0:18:55.36,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:19:00.33,Saku-main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Please give us your signatures to \Nkeep Sakura Hall from closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:02.28,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.74,0:19:04.26,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.74,0:19:04.26,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Jin-san's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.72,0:19:07.19,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please show your support!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.72,0:19:09.42,Saku-thought,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't give up when \NAoyama's working so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.78,0:19:09.52,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.45,0:19:13.65,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't waste my efforts \Non meaningless pursuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:14.84,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.27,0:19:17.29,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,I understand your reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.86,0:19:21.24,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm asking about {\i1}your{\i0} feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.80,0:19:26.79,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you had a painful \Nexperience in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.46,0:19:30.97,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to abandon art and \Nmove away from Mashiro,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.97,0:19:32.12,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.04,0:19:34.65,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,If you're only going to be disappointed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:36.40,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you may as well abandon \Nit before you start.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.78,0:19:38.90,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural to think like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.69,0:19:45.08,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,But I've kept on painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:48.56,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,I still consider Mashiro a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:56.64,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I had Sorata, Nanami, \NMisaki, Jin... and you, Ryunosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.59,0:20:04.00,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke, Sakura Hall must \Nbe important to you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:11.02,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,You have true friends who won't \Nabandon or betray you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.07,0:20:14.38,Saku-main,RITA,0000,0000,0000,,You must treasure those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.85,0:20:23.11,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's work hard again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.49,0:20:24.39,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.39,0:20:26.07,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Those first years...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:33.28,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,They filled in our Nyapollon review \Nsurvey at the culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.67,0:20:35.08,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,They might give us their signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.19,0:20:39.96,Saku-main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,Do I need to sign this one, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:40.89,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.89,0:20:44.01,Saku-main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,I wrote my name in the \Nnotebook in the PC Lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.06,0:20:46.63,Saku-main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,It was on the homepage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.17,0:20:52.23,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:53.76,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,It was in this classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.76,0:20:54.92,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.92,0:20:56.94,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,There was a link on the school's site.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:20:59.65,Sign,PC,0000,0000,0000,,Please give us your signature to keep Sakura Hall open
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.27,0:20:59.65,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Information about Sakura Hall being \Ntorn down is summarized clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:01.40,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Surely not...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.40,0:21:02.75,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotta be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.75,0:21:04.82,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one guy who \Ncould've done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.73,0:21:10.08,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.08,0:21:11.05,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.05,0:21:12.16,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.39,0:21:14.37,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.37,0:21:16.43,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for putting the \Nnotebook in the PC Lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.43,0:21:18.56,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.12,0:21:22.92,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Optimizing an impossible amount\N of work and making it possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:24.43,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,is a programmer's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.43,0:21:25.63,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, get off of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.29,0:21:29.49,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You should have told us \Nyou were working on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.49,0:21:32.18,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Why didn't \Nyou say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.61,0:21:35.00,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A programmer works in silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.28,0:21:38.46,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to feel good about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.46,0:21:40.94,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon, you'll wear a costume and \Ncollect signatures with us starting tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.35,0:21:42.05,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.05,0:21:43.15,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.81,0:22:44.19,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,And that's 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.55,0:22:46.17,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorata.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.99,0:22:47.87,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.01,0:22:53.12,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.12,0:22:54.79,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Counting signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.79,0:22:57.21,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We've got about 300 signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.65,0:23:00.07,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We're still a long way from\N our target of two-thirds, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.03,0:23:03.69,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.20,0:23:06.32,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I like Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.56,0:23:08.96,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,So do I. So does everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.47,0:23:13.05,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Jin-san and Misaki-senpai, \NAoyama and Akasaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:14.58,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Even Chihiro-sensei does.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.87,0:23:17.19,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we protect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.19,0:23:18.15,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.47,0:23:20.89,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I will protect Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.71,0:23:22.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll all do it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.17,0:23:26.96,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:30.22,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It's better together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.53,0:23:34.37,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think collecting \Nsignatures would be this hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.82,0:23:40.98,NextEptitle,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(458,1)}#21 It's Not Anyone's Fault That It Rains
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.37,0:23:35.93,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Can we sign our own names?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.93,0:23:37.73,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't I use this as an opportunity...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.73,0:23:39.64,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to trick Jin into signing \Na marriage register?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.64,0:23:40.98,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, good idea!
